  "question_text": "<div class=\"paragraph\">A couple decides to go to an apple orchard to pick some apples. After searching the orchard for the best looking apples, they decide to pick <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$10$</span> apples from a single tree. When they go to pay, they figure out the average weight of each apple is <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$75$</span> grams. </div><div class=\"paragraph\">Can the couple speculate that the average size of the apples from the farm is <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$75$</span> grams?</div>",
  "image_files": [],
  "choices": [
    {
      "letter": "A",
      "text": "Yes, since they selected\n10\napples, they can safely assume the average weight of all the apples on the farm is\n75\ngrams."
    },
    {
      "letter": "B",
      "text": "Yes, because all samples of\n10\napples will produce a mean weight of\n75\ngrams."
    },
    {
      "letter": "C",
      "text": "Yes, since the apples are random, we can safely assume the mean will be\n75\ngrams for all samples of size\n10"
    },
    {
      "letter": "D",
      "text": "No, due to sampling variability, not all samples of size\n10\nwill have a mean of\n75\ngrams"
    },
    {
      "letter": "E",
      "text": "No, because the Large Counts Condition is not met"
    }
  ],
  "correct_answer": "<strong>Choice 'D'</strong> is the correct answer. ",
